  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Function to calculate only the edges of the bins used by the "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/histogram",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "histogram",
                "text": "histogram"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " function."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Input data. The histogram is computed over the flattened array."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "array_like",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Input data. The histogram is computed over the flattened array."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "a",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "If "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "bins"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is an int, it defines the number of equal-width\nbins in the given range (10, by default). If "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "bins"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is a\nsequence, it defines the bin edges, including the rightmost\nedge, allowing for non-uniform bin widths."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  },
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "If "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "bins"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is a string from the list below, "
                      },
                      {
                        "external_url": "",
                        "href": "/docs/api/ops/histogram_bin_edges",
                        "kind": "link",
                        "target": "histogram_bin_edges",
                        "text": "histogram_bin_edges"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " will\nuse the method chosen to calculate the optimal bin width and\nconsequently the number of bins (see the Notes section for more detail\non the estimators) from the data that falls within the requested range.\nWhile the bin width will be optimal for the actual data\nin the range, the number of bins will be computed to fill the\nentire range, including the empty portions. For visualisation,\nusing the 'auto' option is suggested. Weighted data is not\nsupported for automated bin size selection."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  },
                  {
                    "items": [
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "Minimum bin width between the 'sturges' and 'fd' estimators.\nProvides good all-around performance."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ],
                        "term_inline": [
                          {
                            "kind": "text",
                            "text": "'auto'"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "Robust (resilient to outliers) estimator that takes into\naccount data variability and data size."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ],
                        "term_inline": [
                          {
                            "kind": "text",
                            "text": "'fd' (Freedman Diaconis Estimator)"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "An improved version of Sturges' estimator that works better\nwith non-normal datasets."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ],
                        "term_inline": [
                          {
                            "kind": "text",
                            "text": "'doane'"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "Less robust estimator that takes into account data variability\nand data size."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ],
                        "term_inline": [
                          {
                            "kind": "text",
                            "text": "'scott'"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "Estimator based on leave-one-out cross-validation estimate of\nthe integrated squared error. Can be regarded as a generalization\nof Scott's rule."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ],
                        "term_inline": [
                          {
                            "kind": "text",
                            "text": "'stone'"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "Estimator does not take variability into account, only data\nsize. Commonly overestimates number of bins required."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ],
                        "term_inline": [
                          {
                            "kind": "text",
                            "text": "'rice'"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "R's default method, only accounts for data size. Only\noptimal for gaussian data and underestimates number of bins\nfor large non-gaussian datasets."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ],
                        "term_inline": [
                          {
                            "kind": "text",
                            "text": "'sturges'"
                          }
                        ]
                      },
                      {
                        "blocks": [
                          {
                            "inline": [
                              {
                                "kind": "text",
                                "text": "Square root (of data size) estimator, used by Excel and\nother programs for its speed and simplicity."
                              }
                            ],
                            "type": "paragraph"
                          }
                        ],
                        "term_inline": [
                          {
                            "kind": "text",
                            "text": "'sqrt'"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "definition_list"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "int or sequence of scalars or str, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "If "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "bins"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " is an int, it defines the number of equal-width\nbins in the given range (10, by default). If "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "bins"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " is a\nsequence, it defines the bin edges, including the rightmost\nedge, allowing for non-uniform bin widths."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "bins",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "The lower and upper range of the bins.  If not provided, range\nis simply "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "(a.min(), a.max())"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": ".  Values outside the range are\nignored. The first element of the range must be less than or\nequal to the second. "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "range"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " affects the automatic bin\ncomputation as well. While bin width is computed to be optimal\nbased on the actual data within "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "range"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": ", the bin count will fill\nthe entire range including portions containing no data."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "(float, float), optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "The lower and upper range of the bins.  If not provided, range\nis simply "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "(a.min(), a.max())"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": ".  Values outside the range are\nignored. The first element of the range must be less than or\nequal to the second. "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "range"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " affects the automatic bin\ncomputation as well. While bin width is computed to be optimal\nbased on the actual data within "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "range"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": ", the bin count will fill\nthe entire range including portions containing no data."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "range",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "An array of weights, of the same shape as "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": ".  Each value in\n"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "a"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " only contributes its associated weight towards the bin count\n(instead of 1). This is currently not used by any of the bin estimators,\nbut may be in the future."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "array_like, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "An array of weights, of the same shape as "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "a"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": ".  Each value in\n"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "a"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " only contributes its associated weight towards the bin count\n(instead of 1). This is currently not used by any of the bin estimators,\nbut may be in the future."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "weights",
                "type": "field_list"
              }
            ],
            "title": "Parameters",
            "type": "field_list"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Parameters"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "The edges to pass into "
                      },
                      {
                        "external_url": "",
                        "href": "/docs/api/ops/histogram",
                        "kind": "link",
                        "target": "histogram",
                        "text": "histogram"
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "array of dtype float",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "The edges to pass into "
                  },
                  {
                    "external_url": "",
                    "href": "/docs/api/ops/histogram",
                    "kind": "link",
                    "target": "histogram",
                    "text": "histogram"
                  }
                ],
                "name": "bin_edges",
                "type": "field_list"
              }
            ],
            "title": "Returns",
